  "preFix": {
    "title": "Roasted red pepper soup",
    "subtitle": "Smoky, sweet, and vivid orange",
    "excerpt": "Red peppers roasted until charred and sweet, blended with tomatoes, garlic, and smoked paprika. A vivid, deeply flavoured soup that can be made in under an hour from start to finish.",
    "sourceNotes": "Roasted red pepper soup draws on Spanish and Mediterranean cooking traditions where charring peppers over flame or in the oven to remove skins and intensify flavour is standard practice.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roasting red peppers until the skins blacken and blister removes the tough skin and concentrates the sweetness into something much more intense than the raw pepper. That concentrated base, blended with tinned tomatoes and a little smoked paprika, makes a soup with a depth of flavour that is difficult to achieve any other way. The technique takes confidence the first time but becomes automatic.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
