        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Roast the peppers and tomatoes",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C conventional. Place the halved {{pepper-red}} peppers (skin side up), halved {{tomato}} tomatoes, and {{garlic}} unpeeled garlic cloves on a large roasting tin. Drizzle with oil, season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Roast for 30 to 35 minutes until the pepper skins are ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "charred",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpry26b40000h8v4twaw4jze"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " and blistered. Transfer the peppers to a bowl, cover with a plate or cling film, and leave to steam for 10 minutes. Peel off the skins once cool enough to handle.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Squeeze the garlic cloves out of their skins.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Build and blend the soup",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat a glug of oil in a saucepan over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and cook for 8 minutes until soft. Add {{smoked-paprika}} of smoked paprika and cook for 30 seconds.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the peeled roasted peppers, roasted tomatoes, squeezed garlic, {{tinned-tomatoes}} of tinned tomatoes, and {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Simmer for 10 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Blend in batches until smooth. Pass through a sieve if you want an extra-smooth result. Taste and season.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle into bowls. Add a spoonful of soured cream and a few basil leaves if using.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Leave them covered for the full 10 minutes. The steam softens the bond between skin and flesh. The skin should then peel away in sheets.",
                "cause": "The peppers were not steamed in a covered bowl long enough after roasting.",
                "symptom": "Pepper skins won't come off easily"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add a small splash of sherry vinegar or red wine vinegar. The smoked paprika helps too: use a slightly larger pinch.",
                "cause": "The peppers were very ripe, or the tinned tomatoes were sweet.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too sweet"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use fewer tomatoes and more peppers to brighten the colour. Blend quickly and don't reduce the soup after blending.",
                "cause": "The roasted tomatoes added too much colour, or the soup cooked too long.",
                "symptom": "Colour is brownish rather than vivid orange-red"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use sweet paprika in place of smoked for a milder version. The roasted pepper itself gives plenty of depth.",
                "cause": "Too much smoked paprika.",
                "symptom": "Smoky flavour is too dominant"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "The technique of charring peppers before cooking with them is Spanish in origin: pimientos del piquillo, the small, charred Spanish peppers sold in jars, use exactly this method. The soup version became a British deli and gastropub staple in the 1990s and has stayed there. It is one of those dishes that looks much more complex than it is, which makes it a reliable dinner party starter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 4,
